## CounterStyleStatic.alphabeticFromUnicodeRange property

Create an alphabetic system renderer from a UTF-16 code unit and an alphabet length. The set of symbols for this alphabetic system will be generated by incrementing `originUnicode` with every integer in range \[0, `alphabetLength` - 1\].

See [CSS Counter Styles Level 3, Bijective Numerals: the alphabetic system](https://www.w3.org/TR/css-counter-styles-3/#alphabetic-system)<!-- -->.

<b>Signature:</b>

```typescript
alphabeticFromUnicodeRange: (originUnicode: number, alphabetLength: number) => CounterStyleRenderer;
```
